A building located within the premises of Ile Oodua Palace of Ooni of Ife, Oba Adeyeye Ogunwusi, has been razed down by fire, destroying valuables. According to a source around Enuwa, in the Ile-Ife area of Osun State, where the palace is located, the incident happened around 11:30 pm on Friday. According to a statement by the monarchâ€™s spokesperson, Moses Olafare, there was no casualty or loss of cultural item or injury recorded in the inferno, blaming the incident on power surge.